meaningMnemonic:
A <kanji>male</kanji> <kanji>dog</kanji> is a <vocabulary>male dog</vocabulary>.

It's worth mentioning that you'll see this most often written in katakana, as both オス犬 and オスの犬.
readingMnemonic: The readings are the kun'yomi readings, which is probably A-Okay for 犬, but for 雄 you'll want to think about how a male dog is probably pretty pushy, always trying <reading>to push</reading> (押す) other dogs around, being male and moody and all that.
